{
  "local_port": 49642,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get scholarship for data science in Asia?",
  "response": "There are several scholarships available for students interested in pursuing data science in Asia. These scholarships are offered by universities, governments, and private organizations. Here are some options:\n\n### 1. **Asian Institute of Technology (AIT), Thailand**\n   - **Scholarship**: AIT offers various scholarships for international students, including those pursuing data science-related programs.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to international students with strong academic records.\n   - **Website**: [AIT Scholarships](https://www.ait.ac.th/admissions/scholarships/)\n\n### 2. **Singapore Data Science Consortium (SDSC), Singapore**\n   - **Scholarship**: SDSC offers scholarships for students enrolled in data science programs at Singaporean universities.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to students enrolled in participating universities.\n   - **Website**: [SDSC Scholarships](https://www.sdsc.sg/)\n\n### 3. **National University of Singapore (NUS), Singapore**\n   - **Scholarship**: NUS offers the NUS Graduate Scholarship for students pursuing master's or Ph.D. programs in data science and related fields.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to both domestic and international students.\n   - **Website**: [NUS Scholarships](https://www.nus.edu.sg/registrar/graduate/graduate-programmes/scholarships)\n\n### 4. **University of Tokyo, Japan**\n   - **Scholarship**: The University of Tokyo offers the MEXT Scholarship for international students, which can be used for data science programs.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to international students with excellent academic records.\n   - **Website**: [University of Tokyo Scholarships](https://www.u-tokyo.ac.jp/en/prospective-students/scholarships.html)\n\n### 5. **Indian Institute of Technology (IIT), India**\n   - **Scholarship**: Various IITs offer scholarships for students pursuing data science and related fields at both undergraduate and postgraduate levels.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to Indian and international students.\n   - **Website**: [IIT Scholarships](https://www.iit.ac.in/admissions/scholarships)\n\n### 6. **Hong Kong PhD Fellowship Scheme (HKPFS), Hong Kong**\n   - **Scholarship**: The HKPFS offers scholarships for students pursuing Ph.D. programs in data science and related fields in Hong Kong.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to international students with excellent academic records.\n   - **Website**: [HKPFS](https://cerg1.ugc.edu.hk/hkpfs/index.html)\n\n### 7. **Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology (KAIST), South Korea**\n   - **Scholarship**: KAIST offers scholarships for international students enrolled in data science-related programs.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to international students with strong academic records.\n   - **Website**: [KAIST Scholarships](https://www.kaist.ac.kr/en/html/sub/05_05_01.html)\n\n### 8. **Chinese Government Scholarship (CSC), China**\n   - **Scholarship**: The CSC offers scholarships for international students pursuing master's and Ph.D. programs in data science at Chinese universities.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to international students with excellent academic records.\n   - **Website**: [CSC Scholarships](http://www.csc.edu.cn/Laihua/)\n\n### 9. **Asian Development Bank-Japan Scholarship Program (ADB-JSP)**\n   - **Scholarship**: ADB-JSP offers scholarships for students from ADB member countries to pursue postgraduate studies in data science and related fields.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to nationals of ADB member countries.\n   - **Website**: [ADB-JSP](https://www.adb.org/work-with-us/careers/japan-scholarship-program)\n\n### 10. **University of Malaya, Malaysia**\n   - **Scholarship**: The University of Malaya offers various scholarships for students pursuing data science-related programs.\n   - **Eligibility**: Open to both domestic and international students.\n   - **Website**: [University of Malaya Scholarships](https://www.um.edu.my/about-us/scholarship)\n\n### Application Tips:\n- **Research**: Visit the official websites of the universities and organizations offering scholarships to get detailed information on eligibility, application procedures, and deadlines.\n- **Prepare Documents**: Commonly required documents include academic transcripts, letters of recommendation, a statement of purpose, and proof of language proficiency (e.g., IELTS/TOEFL).\n- **Apply Early**: Start the application process well in advance to meet deadlines and ensure all documents are in order.\n\nBy exploring these options and preparing thoroughly, you can increase your chances of securing a scholarship for data science in Asia.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
